const n="/api/owner",s={getAll:async(r,e)=>{try{const o=new URLSearchParams({ownerId:r,...e}).toString(),t=await fetch(`${n}/booking?${o}`);if(!t.ok)throw new Error("Network response was not ok");return await t.json()}catch(o){throw console.error("Error fetching booking:",o),o}},getById:async(r,e)=>{try{const o=await fetch(`${n}/booking/${e}?ownerId=${r}`);if(!o.ok)throw new Error("Network response was not ok");return await o.json()}catch(o){throw console.error("Error fetching booking details:",o),o}},create:async(r,e)=>{try{const o=await fetch(`${n}/booking`,{method:"POST",headers:{"Content-Type":"application/json"},body:JSON.stringify({...e,ownerId:r})});if(!o.ok)throw new Error("Network response was not ok");return await o.json()}catch(o){throw console.error("Error creating booking:",o),o}},update:async(r,e,o)=>{try{const t=await fetch(`${n}/booking/${e}`,{method:"PUT",headers:{"Content-Type":"application/json"},body:JSON.stringify({...o,ownerId:r})});if(!t.ok)throw new Error("Network response was not ok");return await t.json()}catch(t){throw console.error("Error updating booking:",t),t}},delete:async(r,e)=>{try{const o=await fetch(`${n}/booking/${e}?ownerId=${r}`,{method:"DELETE"});if(!o.ok)throw new Error("Network response was not ok");return await o.json()}catch(o){throw console.error("Error deleting booking:",o),o}}};export{s as b};
